Package inout.paths

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Path
    Path is an object create by the PathParser which stores all necessary information about an Indexing / Lexicon, which is the details about the data (frequency or probability), the directory, the extension (is it an archive?)
    PathHandler
    Class to manage all Path-objects created by a PathParser.
    PathParser
    Parses a .xml-file with Path-descriptions into Path objects.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    UnsetPathAttributeException  
    XMLParseException
